{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"oafish-tidal-groundhog","creation_channel":"cli","description":"The Homebrew formula update (docs/releasing.md step 3) is the only manual release channel and it was silently skipped for 0.8.0 (tap left at 0.7.1 until this session). Automate it WITHOUT a new stored cross-repo token (repo posture is OIDC/no-stored-token for publishing): add a scheduled + workflow_dispatch self-bump workflow IN the tap repo (navapbc/homebrew-rebar) that polls PyPI for the latest nava-rebar, and if newer, updates Formula/rebar.rb url+sha256 and commits with the tap's own GITHUB_TOKEN. Idempotent no-op when current; self-heals missed releases. Update docs/releasing.md step 3 to mark Homebrew automated (manual = fallback). Release v0.9.1 carrying the doc change + 858 (dedup filter that missed 0.9.0).","id":"f12a-b2c2-5e1c-46bb","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["release","homebrew","automation"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Automate Homebrew tap bump (self-bump workflow) + docs; the manual step was skipped for 0.8.0"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784524130192488001,"uuid":"361e35b2-bb6f-4e65-989a-f6fd1e4745a8"}